{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17602162","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17602162"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:23:30+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:23:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15688"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15688","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15688"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.35,0.35,0.16,0.13,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8379"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62243"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8379","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8379"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15688"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47689"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7037"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"10124"},{"type":"tags","id":"10602"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20193"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20195"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62243","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/62243"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EConsider the characteristics of gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) secretion during different phases of the menstrual cycle.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the GnRH pulse pattern during the luteal phase compared to the follicular phase?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Higher amplitude, lower frequency","Lower amplitude, lower frequency","Lower amplitude, higher frequency","Higher amplitude, higher frequency","Equal amplitude and frequency"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring the menstrual cycle, GnRH is released in a pulsatile pattern that varies between phases. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ehigher amplitude, lower frequency\u003C/strong\u003E pattern during the luteal phase is crucial for maintaining corpus luteum function and progesterone secretion. A \u003Cstrong\u003Elower amplitude, lower frequency\u003C/strong\u003E pattern would be insufficient to maintain luteal function. A \u003Cstrong\u003Elower amplitude, higher frequency\u003C/strong\u003E pattern is characteristic of the follicular phase. A \u003Cstrong\u003Ehigher amplitude, higher frequency\u003C/strong\u003E pattern would lead to excessive gonadotropin release. Having \u003Cstrong\u003Eequal amplitude and frequency\u003C/strong\u003E throughout the cycle would not allow for the differential regulation of FSH and LH needed for normal ovarian function.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) pulses during the luteal phase have higher amplitude but lower frequency compared to the follicular phase","Changes in GnRH pulse patterns regulate the differential secretion of follicle-stimulating hormone and luteinizing hormone throughout the menstrual cycle"],"references":["Vigil P, Lyon C, Flores B, Rioseco H, Serrano F. Ovulation, a sign of health. Linacre Q. 2017 Nov;84(4):343-355. doi: 10.1080/00243639.2017.1394053. Epub 2017 Nov 27. PMID: 29255329; PMCID: PMC5730019.","Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebeb